---
import BaseLayout from '#layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Giancarlo Buomprisco" description="About Giancarlo Buomprisco - Software Developer and Founder">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8">About Me</h1>

    <p>
      My name is Giancarlo, and I work as a Software Developer, specialized in
      building web applications with TypeScript.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm originally from Italy, but spent the largest part of the past decade in
      London (UK), where I worked for various companies, especially in the financial
      sector.
    </p>

    <h3>2021-2026</h3>

    <p>
      I run <a href="https://makerkit.dev" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MakerKit</a>
      and <a href="https://formtoro.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Formtoro</a>
      (with a cofounder). I now live in Taipei. I like traveling in Asia, and spend the
      summers in my hometown in Italy.
    </p>

    <h3>2020</h3>

    <p>
      I took on a contract with TradeWeb, one of the most important Electronic
      Trading services in the world. The project involved a difficult transition from
      a Flash/C++ based charting library to a new, Angular and Highcharts stack. We
      were able to swap all the charts before the Flash kill-switch in January 2021.
    </p>

    <h3>2019</h3>

    <p>
      I joined OneTrust, a unicorn in the Privacy space, to grow and lead the
      London's front-end engineering team. Later, I took on a contract with Barclays
      Bank, co-leading a project to build a reusable, customizable framework for
      building interactive forms driven by a custom syntax.
    </p>

    <h3>2017-2018</h3>

    <p>
      I joined Societe Generale, one of the largest banks in Europe. My goal was to
      modernize the stack from Angular.js to modern Angular and ngRx.
    </p>

    <h3>2015-2016</h3>

    <p>
      I worked for Klood, a social-media planner and analytics company, then turned
      market-research analyzer. These were fundamental years in my growth.
    </p>

    <h3>2013-2014</h3>

    <p>
      After my graduation I worked at King's College London, in the Digital
      Humanities Department. Then I joined eFinancialCareers, one of the most
      important job boards in the financial sector.
    </p>

    <h3>2010-2013</h3>

    <p>
      I studied Digital Humanities at University of Pisa, a subject which taught me
      both Computer Science and literary studies.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
